                  <handDesc>
                    <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                      <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#108v #109r #109v" facs="109 110">fols. 108v, 109r, 109v</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                    </handNote></handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                      Decorative designs: <locus target="#4r #22r #49r #62r #74v #100v #118r #119r" facs="004 022 049 062 075 101 118 119">folss. 4r, 22r, 49r, 62r, 74v, 100v, 118r, 119r, </locus> (ornate ḥaräg);
                      <locus target="#14r #27v #37r #56v #74r #85v #88v #94r #112v" facs="014 028 037 057 074 086 089 094 113">14r, 27v, 37r, 56v, 74r, 85v, 88v, 94r, 112v</locus> (lines of alternating red and black dots</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1"><desc type="Asmat"><locus target="#118v" facs="119">Fol. 118v</locus>Asmat prayer to aid in learning. </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a2"><desc type="GuestText"><locus target="#119r #118v" facs="119">f. 119r-118v, lower margin</locus> Excerpt from <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1113Anqasa">ʾAnqaṣa
                                                  bǝrhān</title>, in a later hand. </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e1"><desc>This Psalter seems never to have included <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2509Weddas">Wǝddāse
                                                  Māryām</ref> and <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1113Anqasa">ʾAnqaṣa
                                                  bǝrhān</ref>.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e2"><desc>The covers are damaged. The front board is broken top to bottom, with the grain, about 3.5 cm from the gutter, the back board is broken in about the same place, but repaired with metal wire</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e3"><desc><locus target="#43r" facs="043">Fol. 43r</locus> An elaborate and colorful cross and the text (in red ink), “half is here,” is written in the lower fore edge margin, marking the midpoint of the Psalms. </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a3"><desc><locus target="#118r" facs="118">Fol. 118r</locus> Just above ḥaräg, in a later hand, <q>“Wäldä Iysus, Wäldä Iysus.”</q></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e4"><desc>
                        words of text are written interlinearly, <locus target="#33v #50v #69v" facs="034 051 070">folss. 33v, 50v, 69v, </locus>;
                        and lines of text are written interlinearly, <locus target="#2r #12r #12v #14v" facs="002 012 013 015">2r, 12r, 12v, 14v, </locus>, etc.;
                        and interlinearly with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted, <locus target="#12v" facs="013"> f. 12v, line 20</locus>;
                        erasure markings are visible, <locus target="#47v" facs="048">47v, </locus>;
                        text has been removed, e.g., <locus target="#31r" facs="031">31r</locus></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e6"><desc>
                        The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect
                        ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe reduces the font size at the
                        end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout). This scribe also will complete the line of text above the end of the line
                        (e.g., <locus target="#2r #3r #4r" facs="002 003 004">fols. 2r, 3r, 4r</locus>).</desc></item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
